Flavors of theWorld
Wherever we fly around the globe, we have the enviable job
of tasting and savoring the cuisines of the world. We invite
you to share our discoveries while traveling with us.
Entrees
FILET TIPS DIJON
Dijon, capital of the ancient provence of Burgundy,
is a city of gastronomic reputation. In preparing this typical
specialty, choice filet tidbits are lightly sauteed in butter,
then blended with Dijon style mustard, white burgundy, spices,
beef stock and cream. Complemented by Rissolee potatoes
and a medley of crinkle carrot slices and green beans.
TURKEY CREOLE
Hearty chunks of turkey breast, tomato, celery and green peppers
simmered in a classic New Orleans creole sauce. Accompanied
by a nest of fluffy rice mingled with ripe olive bits and green peas.
OPEN FACED CORNED BEEF PLATE
Lean slices of corned beef stacked high on rye bread
served with a scoop of vegetable macaroni salad,
cottage cheese with pineapple, and assorted relishes.
Aircraft space restrictions
limit the quantities that can be boarded,
and your first choice may not always be available.
Should this oceur, please accept our apologies.
Salad
GARDEN SALAD BOWL
Fresh garden greens in season tossed with an array of
crisp and colorful vegetables . .. garnished with sliced
beets and a Spanish olive. Served with our zesty
Thousand Island Dressing.
Dinner Roll
Creamery Butter
The Sweet Course
DEEP DISH APPLE PIE
A tasty combination of tart apples and cinnamon baked
with an old fashioned pastry crust topping.
